"Nothing," says JFK.

"Then piss off," says Obama. "You know it's all about the Benjamins these days."

Obama turns to walk out. JFK looks at him, then turns to the paper. He stares at it, and then looks up. "Okay," he says, "you are released. You are free to go."

And Obama leaves the house, and goes to play golf. A tall man with orange skin joins him. "Hi," says the man. "Don't tell me JFK tries to recruit you too?"

"Yup," says Obama, and lines up his drive iron.
